  "decision_conditions": [
    "Reason : 1 - The proposed telephone kiosk, by reason of its improper location, design, and high illuminance level, and giving due regard to the existing street furniture and structures present here, would result in an intrusive and inappropriate development within a primarily residential area, and fail to maintain and enhance the appearance, character and pedestrian experience of this section of the public streetscene contrary to Local Plan policies CC1, CC5 and the intent of the National Planning Policy Framework.",
    "Reason : 2 - The applicant has failed to demonstrate that the proposal, by reason of its inappropriate location, design and high illuminance level and giving due regard to the existing street furniture and structures present here, would not result in undue harm to the existing living conditions of the nearby residences, notably the ground floor flats within Wivenhoe Court. It would therefore be contrary to Local Plan policy CC2, CC5, and the intent of the NPPF."
